name: TheAtlantic
text: Key Democrats from the Biden and Sanders wings of the party are backing Jaime Harrison to chair the Democratic National Committee, @isaacdovere reports: https://t.co/W6rlTn8OLf

name: TheAtlantic
text:
RT @IsaacDovere: NEW from me: the pieces are coming together quickly for @harrisonjaime to be the new DNC chair, including @WhipClyburn who says "all of Biden’s friends know what I feel about it.”

https://t.co/0WzlFyTpOm

name: TheAtlantic
text:
House Minority Leader Kevin McCarthy suggested Tuesday that Joe Biden might not be the next president.

In June, @anneapplebaum asked why some Republican leaders have chosen to be complicit with President DonaldTrump’s immoral and dangerous acts. https://t.co/GCrxyNrOKR

name: TheAtlantic
text: "The 2020 electoral outcome—Democratic White House, Republican Senate—was the worst one in terms of getting anything done in the Capitol, and is thus a pending disaster for the country’s sick, unemployed, and poor," @AnnieLowrey writes: https://t.co/IaTJlA4MK5

name: TheAtlantic
text: "A responsible commander in chief would be underscoring the stability and strength of U.S. defense and intelligence agencies during the presidential transition. But that’s not the commander in chief we have," @KoriSchake writes: https://t.co/mtoHz3uYE6

name: TheAtlantic
text: "The American people are entitled to some action from their elected members of Congress, which is constitutionally charged with checking abuses in the executive branch," @kimwehle writes: https://t.co/eSSFCPZF8Z

name: TheAtlantic
text: Joe Biden was perhaps the only candidate who could've tied together a winning Democratic coalition this year, @RonBrownstein writes. https://t.co/ygziiCoug3

name: TheAtlantic
text: Christopher Landon's new body-swap film, "Freaky," is bracingly irreverent without sacrificing the scare factor, a combination that’s been missing from a lot of Hollywood’s horror output in the last decade, @davidlsims writes. https://t.co/BmZ6yO4uEO

name: TheAtlantic
text: "Xi Jinping’s China is an infirm colossus that will be frustrated by unmet ambitions. A strong but frustrated country poses a special kind of danger. This is the China Nightmare," @DAlexBlumenthal writes: https://t.co/F6GqSgyqJB

name: TheAtlantic
text: Twitter created an exemption to its policies specifically so it wouldn't have to ban Donald Trump while he was president. What happens come January? https://t.co/pWgwSI8oLw

name: TheAtlantic
text: For centuries, villagers in Brazil's river towns have blamed pink dolphins for all sorts of heinous crimes. The myth is receding—and now the dolphins are under attack, writes @sushmaaaaaaaa. https://t.co/J8gYzWQCt2
